<comment type="function">
<text evidence="4 5">Serine palmitoyltransferase (SPT). The heterodimer formed with LCB1/SPTLC1 constitutes the catalytic core. The composition of the serine palmitoyltransferase (SPT) complex determines the substrate preference. The SPTLC1-SPTLC2-SPTSSA complex shows a strong preference for C16-CoA substrate, while the SPTLC1-SPTLC2-SPTSSB complex displays a preference for C18-CoA substrate.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="catalytic activity">
<text evidence="4">Palmitoyl-CoA + L-serine = CoA + 3-dehydro-D-sphinganine + CO(2).</text>
</comment>
